00:52:17.360 --> 00:52:23.120
&gt;&gt;Stasha: Well my question is about the Sweet
Home Chicago campaign proposal to possibly

00:52:23.120 --> 00:52:28.200
set aside 20 percent of all TIF funds to affordable
housing and I just wanted to know your take

00:52:28.200 --> 00:52:30.631
on that and, yeah, what your thoughts were
on that.

00:52:30.631 --> 00:52:36.250
&gt;&gt;Rahm Emanuel: One is -- look we have to
deal with affordable housing. Second, we have

00:52:36.250 --> 00:52:42.650
to reform TIF's so before I put more mandates
on TIF's, I gotta a lot of reforms we gotta

00:52:42.650 --> 00:52:46.980
make. TIF's are the fastest growing part of
the city's budget and they're not in the city's

00:52:46.980 --> 00:52:50.070
budget. Get them in the budget.

00:52:50.070 --> 00:52:54.030
Two, bring full transparency to them.

00:52:54.030 --> 00:53:02.410
Three, even after 20 plus years or 30 years
of TIF's being around we still don't have

00:53:02.410 --> 00:53:08.350
a standard that is this TIF reaching its economic
development goals, its job goals? Develop

00:53:08.350 --> 00:53:13.060
that standard so we can measure the progress
of the TIF.

00:53:13.060 --> 00:53:19.400
Third, in some communities, economic development
is gonna be affordable housing. In other communities

00:53:19.400 --> 00:53:26.730
it's gonna be the retail type of commercial
work. Mandating something before I've made

00:53:26.730 --> 00:53:32.461
all the necessary reforms to a TIF process
would be a mistake in my view. In addition

00:53:32.461 --> 00:53:38.030
to that, TIF's are for blighted economic communities
that are struggling. We have to shut down

00:53:38.030 --> 00:53:41.240
the number of the TIF's that are in high rent
areas right now.

00:53:41.240 --> 00:53:42.330
&gt;&gt;David Lieber: Um-hum.

00:53:42.330 --> 00:53:47.320
&gt;&gt;Rahm Emanuel: There's $950 million of unused
TIF funds; some of them have lived past their

00:53:47.320 --> 00:53:52.420
value. And if I shut them down because they're
no longer there and they have surplus, guess

00:53:52.420 --> 00:53:57.180
what -- who wins? The schools win because
the money will go from there back into the

00:53:57.180 --> 00:53:58.880
property taxes to pay for schools.

00:53:58.880 --> 00:54:06.000
So I'm okay with some of them being used for
affordable housing, but not until I get the

00:54:06.000 --> 00:54:15.430
whole TIF process and TIF system reformed.
